ASTANA, Jul 4 (APP): Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif left here on Thursday for Pakistan after attending the Shanghai Cooperation Organization (SCO) summit and SCO Plus Summit in Astana, Kazakhstan.
The prime minister was seen off at the Nur-Sultan Nazarbayev International Airport by Kazakh Vice Prime Minister Kanat Bozumbayev, Pakistani Ambassador to Kazakhstan Noman Bashir, and other diplomatic staff.
